Date: 21/1/1861
Source: Richmond-Atkinson Papers
Author:
Vol / Page: 1/680
Edition: 1960
Quote: Went on to Kapoai ... had dinner - well supplied with pipis but alas no tupakihi ... saw another noteworthy sight ...[sic] a young karoro just out of the nest, running along in a curious human way all by himself.
Notes: (A.S. Atkinson)

Date: 0/0/1946
Source: Journal of the Polynesian Society
Author:
Vol / Page: 55/156
Edition:
Quote: <i>pipi</i>, cockle in general among the Maori: but by Pakeha more applied to Mesodesma australe. Pipi-komore and pipi-taiari was applied to Dentalium, the tusk-shell.
Notes: Andersen Maori Words in English

