Edition:
Quote: <i>pipi</i>(p. 634). The forms <i>peppy, pippy</i>, are solecistic; but <i>pipi</i> is a `Maori name for a bivalve-like cockle' (Sidney J. Baker, letter, 1946) and is therefore ineligible.
